    <h2>Why Choosing FixMyPC Perth Saves Your Practice Money</h2>

    <p>Accounting principals are well placed to understand the cost of reactive IT because they can calculate it precisely. A senior accountant billing at $200 per hour who spends three hours across a week dealing with software failures, waiting for a technician and catching up on backlogged work has incurred a direct cost of $600 in billable time that was not billed. In a practice with three fee-earners, that figure runs to over $1,800 per week during peak periods. Across a BAS quarter and an EOFY period, the cumulative cost of reactive IT frequently exceeds the annual cost of a managed IT plan by a significant margin.</p>

    <p>Managed IT eliminates the variable cost structure that reactive IT creates. You pay a fixed monthly amount that covers monitoring, maintenance, security, unlimited support and scheduled visits. Problems are identified and addressed before they become outages. When something does require attention, it is resolved the same day rather than waiting for a technician's availability to align with the practice's schedule. The time your team retains across a year of proactive IT management translates directly into client work that gets done and billed rather than time spent managing IT problems.</p>

    <p>The security component of managed IT carries its own financial justification that is particularly relevant for accounting firms. The average cost of recovering from a ransomware attack for a small professional services firm without a current tested backup and appropriate security controls in place runs into tens of thousands of dollars, and that figure does not include the client notification obligations, reputational damage or potential regulatory consequences that accompany a breach of the kind of data accounting firms hold. Managed antivirus, encrypted backup and email security, all included in every FixMyPC Perth plan, eliminate that exposure for a monthly cost that is a small fraction of the risk they remove.</p>

    <p>Staff onboarding is another area where managed IT delivers measurable savings that accounting principals rarely cost correctly. Each new graduate or administrator who joins requires a correctly configured device with the right software licences, accounting platform access, ATO portal credentials and security controls. Without a managed IT arrangement, that process typically takes a senior staff member the better part of a full day. Under a managed plan, it is a structured process that is completed correctly, quickly and without drawing on the time of your highest-cost staff.</p>

